 labels = {["strong"]}>
To enable interprocedural analysis, we assign LLVM values to the following groups.

<EnumerationList title="Enumeration values">

<Link id="a5f10072974ec01bdf70a2f2215f44b23a0ba7583639a274c434bbe6ef797115a4" />

</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a5f10072974ec01bdf70a2f2215f44b23a4789f23283b3a61f858b641a1bef19a3" />
<EnumerationListItem name="Memory">

</EnumerationListItem>

</EnumerationList>

The register group represents SSA registers, the return group represents the return values of functions, and the memory group represents in-memory values. An LLVM <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> can technically be in more than one group. It&#39;s necessary to distinguish these groups so we can, for example, track a global variable separately from the value stored at its location.
